3 Section 4. Section 5-2-301, MCA, is amended to read:
4 "5-2-301. Compensation and expenses for members while in session. (1) Legislators are entitled
5 to a salary commensurate to that of the daily rate for an employee earning $10.33 an hour when the regular
6 session of the legislature in which they serve is convened under 5-2-103 for those days during which the
7 legislature is in session. The hourly rate must be adjusted by any statutorily required pay increase For the
8 legislators serving in the legislative session beginning in January 2027, the salary of each legislator must be
9 determined by multiplying 80% times the average hourly wage for the state of Montana, all industry types,
10 posted by the United States bureau of labor statistics from the most recently published quarter of employment
11 and wages data. For the legislators serving in the legislative session beginning in January 2029 and any
12 subsequent biennium, the salary of each legislator must be determined to be equal to the average hourly wage
13 for the state of Montana, all industry types, posted by the United States bureau of labor statistics from the most
14 recently published quarter of employment and wages data. The average hourly rate must be calculated by
15 dividing the average weekly wage by 40 hours. The president of the senate and the speaker of the house must
16 receive an additional $5 a day in salary for those days during which the legislature is in session.
17 (2) Legislators may serve for no salary.
18 (3) Legislators are entitled to a daily allowance, 7 days a week, during a legislative session, as
19 reimbursement for lodging, breakfast, lunch, dinner, and incidental expenses incurred in attending a session.
20 The amount of the daily allowance is equal to the amount an employee of the executive branch of the federal
21 government is generally entitled to receive as per diem for lodging, breakfast, lunch, dinner, and incidental
22 expenses while away from home in the city of Helena but serving in the United States. Expense payments must
23 stop when the legislature recesses for more than 3 days and resume when the legislature reconvenes.
24 (4) Legislators are entitled to a mileage allowance as provided in 2-18-503 for each mile of travel
25 to the place of the holding of the session and to return to their place of residence at the conclusion of the
26 session.
